---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Insurance &amp; Billing — Plans We Accept | AymanCare"
  description="AymanCare accepts most major insurance including Medicare, Medicaid, Tricare, Aetna, BCBS, Cigna and UnitedHealthcare. HSA/FSA welcome."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Do I need a referral to visit AymanCare?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Most insurance plans do not require a referral for primary care or urgent care visits. If your plan is an HMO that requires referrals for specialist visits, we can help coordinate that during your appointment.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What if my insurance isn't listed?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"We work with many plans beyond those listed above. Call your nearest clinic and we'll check your specific plan. We're continually adding new insurance partnerships.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can I use my HSA or FSA at AymanCare?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes. We accept Health Savings Account (HSA) and Flexible Spending Account (FSA) cards for copays, deductibles, and self-pay visits.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Do you offer payment plans?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes. If you have a balance after insurance processing, we can arrange a payment plan that works for your budget. Just speak with our front desk team.\"}}]}"} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://aymancare.com/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Insurance\",\"item\":\"https://aymancare.com/insurance/\"}]}"} />
  </Fragment>
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="breadcrumbs fade-in">
    <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">✦</span><a href="/about/">About</a><span class="sep">✦</span><span>Insurance</span>
  </div>
  <h1 class="page-title fade-in">Insurance &<br><em>billing.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-subtitle fade-in">We accept most major insurance plans, including Medicare and Tricare. If your plan isn't listed, call us — chances are we work with it.</p>
</section>

<!-- Accepted plans -->
<section class="svc-grid-band">
  <div class="svc-grid-band-inner">
    <span class="overline fade-in" style="margin-bottom: 16px; display: block;">◆ Accepted plans</span>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-in" style="font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);">Plans we <em>accept.</em></h2>
    <div class="three-col" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="mini-card fade-in">
        <div class="num">Commercial</div>
        <h4>Private <em>insurance</em></h4>
        <p>Aetna · Blue Cross Blue Shield · Cigna · UnitedHealthcare · Humana · Ambetter · Oscar · Molina · Community Health Choice</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-card fade-in">
        <div class="num">Government</div>
        <h4>Public <em>programs</em></h4>
        <p>Medicare · Medicaid · Tricare · VA Community Care · CHIP · Texas Health Steps</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-card fade-in">
        <div class="num">Self-Pay</div>
        <h4>No insurance? <em>No problem.</em></h4>
        <p>Transparent self-pay rates · HSA/FSA accepted · Employer-sponsored plans · Workers' compensation</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="fade-in" style="margin-top: 32px; color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 15px;">Not sure if we're in-network? <a href="/contact/" style="color: var(--blue); border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;">Call your nearest clinic</a> and we'll verify your benefits before your visit.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- How billing works -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="svc-main">
    <aside class="svc-aside">
      <div class="aside-card fade-in">
        <div class="l">✦ Bring to your visit</div>
        <h3>What you <em>need</em></h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Photo ID (driver's license or passport)</li>
          <li>Insurance card (front and back)</li>
          <li>Copay (if applicable)</li>
          <li>List of current medications</li>
          <li>Referral letter (if required by your plan)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="aside-card dark fade-in">
        <div class="l">✦ Questions about your bill?</div>
        <h3>We're here to <em>help.</em></h3>
        <a href="/contact/" class="big-num">View all locations →</a>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65); font-size: 13px; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 20px;">Our front desk team can walk you through your bill, explain your coverage, or set up a payment plan.</p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-accent" style="width: 100%; justify-content: center;">Contact us →</a>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <div class="svc-content">
      <h2>How <em>billing</em> works at AymanCare.</h2>
      <p>We believe healthcare billing shouldn't be confusing. Here's how it works: you check in, we verify your insurance on the spot, you pay any copay at the time of service, and we handle the rest with your insurance company directly. If there's a remaining balance after your plan processes the claim, we'll send a clear, itemized statement.</p>

      <h2>Insurance <em>verification.</em></h2>
      <p>Before your visit, our front desk can verify your insurance benefits so you know what to expect. We check your copay amount, deductible status, and whether any referrals are needed. If you'd like us to verify ahead of time, call us with your insurance details and we'll do the legwork before you arrive.</p>

      <blockquote>"We want you thinking about your health at your visit, not your bill. That's why we verify everything upfront."</blockquote>

      <h2>Self-pay & <em>uninsured</em> patients.</h2>
      <p>No insurance? We offer transparent, competitive self-pay rates for all of our services. We accept cash, credit cards, HSA/FSA accounts, and can set up payment plans for larger balances. Our goal is to make sure cost never stands between you and the care you need.</p>

      <h2>Frequently asked <em>questions.</em></h2>

      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Do I need a referral?</h3>
      <p>Most insurance plans do not require a referral for primary care or urgent care visits. If your plan is an HMO that requires referrals for specialist visits, we can help coordinate that during your appointment.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; margin-bottom: 12px;">What if my insurance isn't listed?</h3>
      <p>We work with many plans beyond those listed above. Call your nearest clinic and we'll check your specific plan. We're continually adding new insurance partnerships.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Can I use my HSA or FSA?</h3>
      <p>Yes. We accept Health Savings Account (HSA) and Flexible Spending Account (FSA) cards for copays, deductibles, and self-pay visits.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Do you offer payment plans?</h3>
      <p>Yes. If you have a balance after insurance processing, we can arrange a payment plan that works for your budget. Just speak with our front desk team.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="big-cta">
  <div class="big-cta-inner">
    <span class="overline fade-in">◆ Ready to book?</span>
    <h2 class="fade-in">Don't let insurance<br>questions <em>wait.</em></h2>
    <p class="fade-in">Call us and we'll verify your benefits before your visit — so you can focus on your health, not your paperwork.</p>
    <div class="cta-row fade-in">
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Call your nearest clinic</a>
      <a href="/book-online/" class="btn btn-outline">Book online</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</Base>
